\begin_layout Subsection
Subgame Perfect Equilibrium
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is impossible to apply backward induction in an infinite-length game.
 A subgame NE generalizes backward induction to infinite games.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A 
\series bold
subgame 
\series default
is the set of all nodes after a particular node in the game tree.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A 
\series bold
subgame perfect NE
\series default
 is a profile of strategies that is a NE in all subgames of the game.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If a country does not pay ransom to kidnappers - it is known, and kidnappers
